'''Kawata Shrine''' (かわたじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} enshrined in {{ill|lt=Konan|Q857194|qid=Q857194|1=Konan, Shiga}}, {{ill|lt=Shiga Prefecture|Q131358|qid=Q131358|1=Shiga Prefecture}}. It is a candidate shrine for a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|qid=Q134917286}} and its former rank was {{ill|lt=village shrine|Q134917284|qid=Q134917284|1=Son-sha}}.

=== Enshrined deity ===
It enshrines {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Ame-no-Koyane-no-Mikoto|1=Ame-no-Koyane|qid=Q2564508}}.

=== History ===
The founding period is unknown. It is one of the candidate shrines for a {{ill|lt=Myojin Taisha|Q9610964|qid=Q9610964|1=Myōjin Taisha}} listed in the ''{{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}''. In October 1876 (Meiji 9), it was ranked as a village shrine.

=== Shrine crest ===
* Mitsubā

=== Festivals ===
* Annual festival - May 1

